   "source": [
    "# Trinity Hippocampal Learning Probe — Belief Update Under Correction\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task 2 of 25** | Track 1: Learning | Brain Zone: HIPPOCAMPUS\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook measures a model's ability to update beliefs when corrected.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Trinity Neuroanatomical Foundation\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Hippocampus** in Trinity implements episodic memory reconsolidation:\n",
    "\n",
    "```zig\n",
    "// src/tri/brain/hippocampus_training.zig\n",
    "pub fn reconsolidateEpisode(\n",
    "    cache: *PopulationCache,\n",
    "    new_info: Episode\n",
    ") !void {\n",
    "    // Invalidate stale entries and update with new learning\n",
    "}\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Ternary Scoring {-1, 0, +1}\n",
    "\n",
    "- **+1 (correct)**: Model updates belief correctly\n",
    "- **0 (partial)**: Model shows uncertainty during update\n",
    "- **-1 (wrong)**: Model resists correction or overconfident\n",
    "\n",
    "### φ-Scaling\n",
    "\n",
    "Depth of consequences follows Fibonacci: 1, 2, 3, 5, 8 hops"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install Kaggle Benchmarks SDK\n",
    "!pip install -q kaggle-benchmarks"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import kaggle_benchmarks as kbench\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from dataclasses import dataclass\n",
    "from typing import Literal\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load generated dataset\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../../data/thlp_learning.csv')\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(df)} items\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Filter for belief update task\n",
    "belief_df = df[df['task'] == 'Belief Update Under Correction'].copy()\n",
    "print(f\"Belief update items: {len(belief_df)}\")\n",
    "belief_df[['id', 'task', 'question', 'answer', 'context_length', 'difficulty']].head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define structured output for belief update\n",
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class BeliefUpdateResponse:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Model's response after correction.\"\"\"\n",
    "    corrected_belief: str  # Updated belief\n",
    "    acceptance_level: float  # 0.0 (rejects) to 1.0 (accepts fully)\n",
    "    uncertainty: float  # Model's expressed uncertainty\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def ternary_score(self, expected_answer: str) -> Literal[-1, 0, 1]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Return Trinity ternary score {-1, 0, +1}.\"\"\"\n",
    "        # Correct: updated belief matches expected\n",
    "        if self.corrected_belief == expected_answer:\n",
    "            return 1\n",
    "        # Partial: accepts but with uncertainty\n",
    "        elif 0.4 < self.acceptance_level < 0.8 and self.uncertainty > 0.3:\n",
    "            return 0\n",
    "        # Wrong: rejects or overconfident\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return -1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"BeliefUpdateResponse schema defined\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define Kaggle benchmark task\n",
    "@kbench.task(name=\"trinity_hippocampus_belief_update\")\n",
    "def belief_update(\n",
    "    llm: kbench.LLM,\n",
    "    question: str,\n",
    "    expected_answer: str,\n",
    "    context_length: int\n",
    ") -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Measure model's belief update ability.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Update score: 1.0 (perfect) to -1.0 (worst)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    prompt = f\"\"\"You previously held a belief that was corrected.\n",
    "\n",
    "Question: {question}\n",
    "\n",
    "Provide:\n",
    "1. Your corrected belief\n",
    "2. Your level of acceptance (0.0 to 1.0)\n",
    "3. Your uncertainty about this correction (0.0 to 1.0)\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    response = llm.prompt(\n",
    "        prompt,\n",
    "        schema=BeliefUpdateResponse\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate ternary score\n",
    "    ternary = response.ternary_score(expected_answer)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Combine: 50% correctness, 30% acceptance, 20% uncertainty\n",
    "    correctness = 1.0 if response.corrected_belief == expected_answer else -1.0\n",
    "    acceptance_score = (response.acceptance_level - 0.5) * 2  # [-1, 1]\n",
    "    uncertainty_penalty = response.uncertainty * 0.2  # [0, 0.2]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    final_score = 0.5 * correctness + 0.3 * acceptance_score - uncertainty_penalty\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return max(-1.0, min(1.0, final_score))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Task 'trinity_hippocampus_belief_update' registered\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run evaluation on a sample\n",
    "sample_df = belief_df.head(10)  # Test with 10 items first\n",
    "\n",
    "results = belief_update.evaluate(\n",
    "    llm=[kbench.llm],  # Default test LLM\n",
    "    evaluation_data=sample_df\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Evaluation Results (Sample):\")\n",
    "print(f\"Mean Score: {results['score'].mean():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Std Dev: {results['score'].std():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Min: {results['score'].min():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Max: {results['score'].max():.4f}\")\n",
    "results.head()"
   ]
  },
